Merge pull request #6 from MengTo/feature/loading

Refactor LoadingView API for a better world

Refactor showLoading() and hideLoading() to UIView extension

- Makes code nicer
- Prevents using a global variable for all loading indicators
- Allows multiple loading view simultaneously
- Removing after completion so it cleans up itself
Add a nil condition for loadingView.

- Animations on images in Login screen.
- Font for login text in Stories VC.

- Loading icon changed.
- Loading duration slightly slower.
- Change font for back button.
DesignableTabBarController – because they're so damn hard to customizable.
Storing all animations in Storyboard and removed layer.alpha = 0.

- Autostart: this is for Storyboard, allows you to autostart your animation without a single line of code.
- Autohide: this is mostly for not having to add a "layer.alpha = 0" in viewDidLoad. Without doing this, you'll see the current state of your UI before animation.
- Using custom awakeFromNib and didMoveToWindow instead since for some reason, it gets called only once instead of a crazy amount of times.
- Removed opacity from IBInspectables
animateFrom no longer inspectable. didMoveToWindow() and didMoveToSuperView()
